                <div class="comment-content">
                    <p>Um, wow that looks phenomenal! My dad lived in Savannah, GA for 20 years and when I'd go to visit, our main side dish with steak and potatoes was a vidalia onion. A whole one for each of us (but they're fairly small). You hollow out a hole in the top, drop a beef bouillon cube and butter into it, wrap it in foil and bake for at least an hour. Was always so good combined with a bite of steak and mash!</p>
