                <div class="comment-content">
                    <p>You never put hot glass in the cold sink. You need a trivet to set it on till it cools. A trivet can be made out of a couple of chopsticks laid to form a square or triangle.<br />
Onions are always included in my recipes. I love onions. Try this recipe<br />
Take a onion cut top and bottom off , take of dry skins. Cut it into quarters but leave attached . Take a square of aluminum foil and place the onion on it. Put a teaspoon of butter on it and then pour a small amount of balsamic vinegar on it. Completely cover the onion with the foil an bake at 300 degrees for about 45 minutes.</p>
